<DocsLayout title="Rahinan (Holy Days) - Balinese Calendar" description="Understanding Balinese holy days and ceremonies">
	<h1 class="font-display text-4xl gold-accent mb-8">Rahinan (Holy Days)</h1>

	<p class="text-lg mb-6">
		Rahinan refers to holy days and special ceremonial occasions in the Balinese calendar.
	</p>

	<h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-balinese-gold mt-12 mb-6">Major Holy Days</h2>

	<h3 class="font-body text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Major Rahinan</h3>

	<p class="mb-4">The most important holy days in the Balinese calendar:</p>

	<ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mb-8">
		<li><strong>Galungan</strong> - Buda Kliwon Dungulan (every 210 days)</li>
		<li><strong>Kuningan</strong> - Saniscara Kliwon Kuningan (10 days after Galungan)</li>
		<li><strong>Nyepi</strong> - Tilem Kasanga (Balinese New Year)</li>
		<li><strong>Saraswati</strong> - Saniscara Umanis Watugunung</li>
	</ul>

	<h3 class="font-body text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Tumpek Ceremonies</h3>

	<p class="mb-6">Special Saniscara Kliwon ceremonies that occur every 35 days:</p>

	<ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mb-8">
		<li><strong>Tumpek Landep</strong> - Saniscara Kliwon Landep</li>
		<li><strong>Tumpek Uduh</strong> - Saniscara Kliwon Wariga</li>
		<li><strong>Tumpek Krulut</strong> - Saniscara Kliwon Krulut</li>
			<li><strong>Tumpek Kandang</strong> - Saniscara Kliwon Uye</li>
		<li><strong>Tumpek Wayang</strong> - Saniscara Kliwon Wayang</li>
	</ul>

	<h3 class="font-body text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Other Holy Days</h3>

	<ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mb-8">
		<li><strong>Kajeng Keliwon</strong> - Kajeng (Triwara) + Kliwon (Pancawara)</li>
		<li><strong>Hari Bhatara Sri</strong> - Buda Wage (agricultural fertility day)</li>
		<li><strong>Anggar Kasih</strong> - Anggara (Tuesday) Kliwon (Pancawara)</li>
		<li><strong>Siwa Ratri</strong> - Tilem Kapitu (dark moon)</li>
		<li><strong>Purnama/Tilem</strong> - Full moon/new moon of any sasih</li>
	</ul>


